#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Rule "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 17. Chaphassāyatanasutta → āyatanasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | āyatana (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Chaphassāyatanasutta "
msgstr "17. The Six Fields of Contact "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.113, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.17:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.17:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha was educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "sn4.17:1.3"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā dhammaṃ suṇanti. "
msgstr "And those mendicants were paying heed, paying attention, engaging wholeheartedly, and lending an ear. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.252, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Māra thought, "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sappahaṃseti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama is educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.3"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā dhammaṃ suṇanti. "
msgstr "And those mendicants are paying heed, paying attention, engaging wholeheartedly, and lending an ear. "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ vicakkhukammāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go and pull the wool over their eyes?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: undrīyati → udrīyati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato avidūre mahantaṃ bhayabheravaṃ saddamakāsi, apissudaṃ pathavī maññe undrīyati. Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and made a terrifyingly loud noise close by him. It seemed as if the earth were shattering, so that one of the mendicants said to another, "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.6"
msgid "“bhikkhu bhikkhu, esā pathavī maññe undrīyatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, mendicant, it seems like the earth is shattering!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When this was said, the Buddha said to that mendicant, "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.8"
msgid "“nesā, bhikkhu, pathavī undrīyati. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, that’s not the earth shattering. "

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.9"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tumhākaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato”ti. "
msgstr "That’s Māra the Wicked come to pull the wool over your eyes!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.1"
msgid "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā, "
msgstr "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.2"
msgid "phassā dhammā ca kevalā; "
msgstr "touches, and thoughts, the lot of them—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.3"
msgid "Etaṃ lokāmisaṃ ghoraṃ, "
msgstr "this is the dreadful bait "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.4"
msgid "ettha loko vimucchito. "
msgstr "that the world’s infatuated by. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.1"
msgid "Etañca samatikkamma, "
msgstr "But a mindful disciple of the Buddha "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.2"
msgid "sato buddhassa sāvako; "
msgstr "has transcended all that. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.3"
msgid "Māradheyyaṃ atikkamma, "
msgstr "Having gone beyond Māra’s sovereignty, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.4"
msgid "ādiccova virocatī”ti. "
msgstr "they shine like the sun.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.17:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
